//		Tadb_Deleted.txt : Complement to Tadb.txt containing
//					 All deleted product	
//
//  It is now HySelect when reading this file that will set all 'CDB::Hydrothing::isDeleted' to 1
//  and automatically change the article number with *.
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

new:CDB_Product(ADAP_FUSION_3250_02) -> CVADAPTER_TAB
{
	{
		{
			1													// isDeleted
			1                                                   // isAvailable
			0                                                   // isHidden
			1                                                   // isFix
			0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX
		NO_ID
		DBL_MAX
		DBL_MIN
	}
	"22412-101100"
	"Adapter 02"
	ADAPTYP_CV
	ADAPTFAM_FUSION
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"Adapter for TA-MC100 FSE/FSR actuator"
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                                         // Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the series of the accessory 
	1                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately
	NO_ID                                      	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
}

new:CDB_Product(ADAP_FUSION_3250_01) -> CVADAPTER_TAB
{
	{
		{
			0 								// isDeleted
			1                               // isAvailable
			0                               // isHidden
			1                               // isFix
			0                               // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                               // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               				// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX                     // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                           // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		DBL_MAX                         // Tmax in °C
		DBL_MIN                     	// Tmin in °C
	}
	"22412-001055"                  // Reference to the TA Product
	"Adapter 01"                    // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ADAPTYP_CV                      // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ADAPTFAM_FUSION                 // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID							// Identifier of the version of the product
	1								// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_ADAP_FUSION_3250_01"		// TA-SLIDER 750, TA-MC55(Y)				// IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"							// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           // Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID							// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             // Price of the product
	#eAccessory                     // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	NO_ID                           // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	1                               // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                           // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID							// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
}

////////////////////
// EMO 35 & 85 (VSI)
////////////////////

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(EMO35F) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0													// isDeleted
					1                                                   // isAvailable
					0                                                   // isHidden
					1                                                   // isFix
					0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0 \ DBL_MAX									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
				DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
			}
			"-"
			"EMO35F"
			ACTTYP_ELEC                                 // Identifier of the actuator type
			ACTFAM_EMO35                                // Identifier of the family of the product
			NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the actuator version
			1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                          // Description of the product
			"NO_ID"										// Product image ID
			NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              		// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Circular
		4.0e+0										// Max force or torque developed by the actuator
		-1.0										// Min stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_No						// Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		95.0										// Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		NO_ID
		DBL_MIN										// Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		DBL_MAX										// Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	110*
	"54"
	""
	POW_24VAC \ POW_24VDC
	FREQ_50
	SIG_ON-OFF \ SIG_3POINT
	NO_ID
	#eFailSafeNone
	1													// 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
	RELAY_NO											// Type of relay.
	0													// Number of binary input.
	#eDRP_None

new:CDB_CommissioningSet(MD41DN15A_CS\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0													// isDeleted
					0                                                   // isAvailable
					0                                                   // isHidden
					1                                                   // isFix
					1                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6
				NO_ID
				120.0
				-10.0
			}
			"52176-115&52150-014"
			"MD 41 DN15"
			RVTYPE_CS
			FAM_MD41
			VERS_PT90
			1
			""
			"TA_CS"
			NO_ID
			#ePartOfaSetNo
			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0
			#eProduct                              			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       		// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID											// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL
		DN_15
		CONN_THREAD
		NO_ID
		NO_ID
		"MD41"
		"15"
		"1/2"
		1
		"3A"
		0.0
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointMeasStatOut
		#eMeasDataDpSignal | #eMeasDataFlow
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_MD01DN15
	C_STAD015
}

	{
		{
			{
				{
					0													// isDeleted
					1                                                   // isAvailable
					0                                                   // isHidden
					1                                                   // isFix
					0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).			
				}
				0 \ DBL_MAX									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
				DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
			}
			"61025-001"

			ACTFAM_MC                               	// Identifier of the family of the product
			NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the actuator version
			1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                          // Description of the product
			"NO_ID"										// Product image ID
			NO_ID                                    // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              		// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)

			NO_ID                                   	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Linear
		2.5e+2
		-1.0										// Min stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_No						// Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		9.0e-3										// Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		ADAGR_25									// Identifier of the actuator adapter group
		DBL_MIN										// Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		DBL_MAX										// Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	16000* \ 11000
	"54"
	"30"
	POW_24VAC
	FREQ_50-60
	SIG_3POINT
	NO_ID
	#eFailSafeNone
	1
	RELAY_NO											// Type of relay.
	0													// Number of binary input.
	#eDRP_None

		0														// isDeleted
		1                                                       // isAvailable
		0                                                       // isHidden
		1                                                       // isFix
		0                                                       // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
		0                                                       // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
		0               										// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
	}
	"32220291412"                                          	// Reference to the TA Product
	"TA-FUSION-P 6" + TA-SLIDER 750 (24V)"                  // Name of the product
	FUSION_P150C                                            // Identifier of the control valve
	SLIDER750-STD-24										// Identifier of the actuator
	NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the accessory group
	"USA-International"										// String to allow to apply some filter.
	"NO_ID"			                                        // Identifier of the next ID to consider can be Set ID, Group ID, Product ID etc...
}

	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0							// isDeleted
							1                           // isAvailable
							0                           // isHidden
							1                           // isFix
							0                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                           // Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
							0							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}                               
						2.5e+6 \ 2.5e+6				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                       // Tmax in °C
						-10.0                       // Tmin in °C
					}
					"52754-120"					// Reference to the TA Product
					"KT 512 DN15/20 LF"         // Name of the product

					FAM_KT512                   // Identifier of the family of the product

					1                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]

					"PX_KT512_20"               // Product image ID
					NO_ID                       // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo              // Boolean indicating if the valve is part of a ActSet
					NO_ID						// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.

					NO_ID                       // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)

					NO_ID                       // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth

				}
				BDY_DUCTIRON				// Identifier of the body material
				DN_15                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size

				""                          // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II

				""                          // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                           // CBI compatibility Index
				""                          // CBI Version (5L -> Doesn't exist to allow to get it in TA-Scope but not in CBI)
				5.0e+5                      // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone             // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone				// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

				NO_ID						// Identifier of the outlet size ID

// Remark: Kv values are invented ones (By Jean-Christophe Carette) and not used since KTM 50 has no test points.

new:CDB_PICVCharacteristic(CPICV_KTM50_100FC15\1) -> PICV_CHAR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			#eDISCRETE_Undefined								// #eDISCRETE_True, #eDISCRETE_False or #eDISCRETE_Undefined
			#eTURN_Undefined                                    // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
			0.02												// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
		}
		1.0                                                 // Min measurable setting (For TA-Scope)
		3.0                                                 // Min recommended setting (for selection)
		1                                                   // Number of curves: 1 = Kv catalogue only; 4 = Kv catalogue, Lambda, Re* and Kv from test.
		0.00 \ 0.14                                  		// opening 1 \ Kv 1
		1.00 \ 4.61
		2.00 \ 7.14
		3.00 \ 10.82
		4.00 \ 17.22
		5.00 \ 25.43
		6.00 \ 40.56
		7.00 \ 66.79
		8.00 \ 107.83
		9.00 \ 159.94
		10.0 \ 217.37
	}
	120													// Kvd = Kvs of the Dp controller
	1.5e+4                                              // Fc = Pressure drop in the throttle

{
	{
		{
			#eDISCRETE_Undefined								// #eDISCRETE_True, #eDISCRETE_False or #eDISCRETE_Undefined
			#eTURN_Undefined                                    // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
			0.0													// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
		}
		0.0                                                 // Min measurable setting (for TA-Scope)
		0.0                                                 // Min recommended setting (for selection)
		0                                                   // Number of curves: 1 = Kv catalogue only; 4 = Kv catalogue, Lambda, Re* and Kv from test.
	}
	70													// Kvd = Kvs of the Dp controller
	1.2e+4                                              // Fc = Pressure drop in the throttle
	4.1666666667e-3                                     // Max flow of the valve
	0                                                   // Number of curves: 0 = no curve; 1 = Qmax curve; 2 = Qmax and Dpmin curve
}

new:CDB_StringID(FAM_KTCM512\1) ->FAMILY_TAB

	{

				#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpStab | #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn	// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

///////////////////////////////////////////
//P0 = 1140*qN^(-0.87)-(qN/1000)^2/3.5^2-0.5			qN[l/h] P0[bar]
//P0 = 1140*(qN*3.6e6)^(-0.87)-(qN*3600)^2/3.5^2-0.5	qN[m3/s] P0[Pa]
///////////////////////////////////////////
// C / CF 10.1 compressor
new:CDB_TBCurve(TBC_CMPRS_C_10_1_CF)->TBPUMPCOMPRESSCURVE_TAB
{
	{
		1						// Number of functions associated to the abscissa.
		1.27222222222E-04 \ 5.003039200443E+05
		2.24833333333E-04 \ 2.810108698288E+05
		3.22444444444E-04 \ 1.847913184875E+05
		4.20055555556E-04 \ 1.266068403782E+05
		5.17666666667E-04 \ 8.446528394490E+04
		6.15277777778E-04 \ 5.004646439763E+04
	}
	1.272e-4 \ 6.153e-4		// Min \ Max equalizing flow
	5e4 \ 5e5				// Min \ Max Target pressure min \ max
	"C 10.1"				// Curve name
}

////// Compressor C10.1 F

		CDB_TBCurve::CurveName = "CPV 10.1"
	}

new:CDB_TecBox(COMP_C10_1_3F)->TECBOX_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				0													// isDeleted
				1                                                   // isAvailable
				0                                                   // isHidden
				1                                                   // isFix
				0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
				0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
				0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
			}
			3e+5 \ 3e+5 		// in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
			NO_ID				// Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
			70					// Tmax in °C
			5					// Tmin in °C
		}
		"810-1010"				// Reference to the Product
		"C 10.1-3 F"			// Name of the product
		TBXTYPE_COMPRESSO		// Identifier of the product type 
		TBXFAM_COMPR_C			// Identifier of the family of the product
		NO_ID					// Identifier of the version of the product
		1						// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
		""						// Product comment
		"NO_ID"	//TODO			// Product image ID
		NO_ID	//TODO			// Identifier of the accessory group
		#ePartOfaSetNo			// Boolean indicating if the valve is part of a ActSet
		NO_ID					// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
		0.0						// Price of the product
		#eProduct               // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
		NO_ID                   // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
		0                       // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
		NO_ID                   // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
		NO_ID					// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
	}
	"22"					// Enclosure protection 
	POW_230VAC				// List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
	FREQ_50					// Accepted frequency
	600						// Power consumption
	59						// Sound pressure level only for compresso and vento
	1						// Nbre of compressors/pump 0/1/2 ( 0 for CX )
	TBC_CMPRS_C_10_1_CF   	// PumpCompressCurveID
	1e+4					// Accuracy in Pascal
	#eVesselTop				// InstallationLayout	#eWallHanged/#eFloorStanding/#eFloorStandingNextTo/#eFloorStandingInFront/#eVesselTop
	0.3						// Height
	0.41					// Width	
	0.46					// Depth
	15						// Weight double (kg)
	#ePMFunc_Compressor		// Functions 			#ePMFunc_None/#ePMFunc_Degasing/#ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp/#ePMFunc_Compressor/#ePMFunc_Pump geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
	#ePMFunc_None			// FunctionsExclusion 	#ePMFunc_None, #ePMFunc_Degasing, #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp, #ePMFunc_Compressor or #ePMFunc_Pump should be a geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
	#ePMVariant_None		// TecBox Variant		#ePMVariant_None/#ePMVariant_Cooling/#ePMVariant_EcoAuto/#ePMVariant_BreakTank/#ePMVariant_VacuumDegassing/#ePMVariant_ExternalAir/#ePMVariant_IntBufferVssl/#ePMVariant_HighFlowTemp
	-1.0					// Max admissible temperature for WM (~30°C)
	PLENOGROUP_TECBOX		// Identifier of the Pleno group that match the tecbox.
	NO_ID					// Identifier of the buffer vessel ID if fixed.
	NO_ID					// WaterTreatmentCombID		Identifier of the different combination of the water treatment.
	-1						// MaxSecondaryVessels: Maximum allowed secondary vessel. If -1 we take the 'm_iMaxNumberOfVesselsInParallel' - 1 from the technical parameters.
}

	#ePMFunc_Pump 			//Functions: #ePMFunc_None/#ePMFunc_Degasing/#ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp/#ePMFunc_Compressor/#ePMFunc_Pump geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
	#ePMFunc_None			// FunctionsExclusion: #ePMFunc_None, #ePMFunc_Degasing, #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp, #ePMFunc_Compressor or #ePMFunc_Pump should be a geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
	#ePMVariant_None		//TecBox Variant		#ePMVariant_None/#ePMVariant_Cooling/#ePMVariant_EcoAuto/#ePMVariant_BreakTank/#ePMVariant_VacuumDegassing/#ePMVariant_ExternalAir/#ePMVariant_IntBufferVssl/#ePMVariant_HighFlowTemp
	-1.0					//Max admissible temperature for WM (~30°C)
	PLENOGROUP_TECBOX		//Identifier of the Pleno group that match the tecbox.
	NO_ID					//Identifier of the buffer vessel ID if fixed.	
	NO_ID					//WaterTreatmentCombID		Identifier of the different combination of the water treatment.
	-1 						// MaxSecondaryVessels: Maximum allowed secondary vessel. If -1 we take the 'm_iMaxNumberOfVesselsInParallel' - 1 from the technical parameters.
}

///////////////////////////////////////////
// From the Pneumatex equation, we transform to adapt to SI units.
// And in HySelect we use the curve with pman instead of p0.
// p0 =  -8.0*10^(-8.0)*qN^2.08+0.00033*qN+17.57-(qN/1000)^2/3.4^2									qN[l/h]  p0[bar]
// p0 = (-8.0*10^(-8.0)*(qN*3.6e6)^2.08+0.00033*qN*3.6e6+17.57 -(qN*3600)^2/3.4^2)*100000			qN[m3/s] p0[Pa]
// pman = (-8.0*10^(-8.0)*(qN*3.6e6)^2.08+0.00033*qN*3.6e6+17.57 -(qN*3600)^2/3.4^2+0.5)*100000		qN[m3/s] pman[Pa]
///////////////////////////////////////////
//   TPV 19.2 P pump
new:CDB_TBCurve(TBC_PUMP_T_19_2)->TBPUMPCOMPRESSCURVE_TAB
{
	{
		1						// Number of functions associated to the abscissa.
		1.28194444444E-03 \ 1.44042255738E+06
		1.35246913580E-03 \ 1.38854100462E+06
		1.42299382716E-03 \ 1.33325941642E+06
		1.49351851852E-03 \ 1.27456847900E+06
		1.56404320988E-03 \ 1.21245929425E+06
		1.63456790123E-03 \ 1.14692334282E+06
		1.70509259259E-03 \ 1.07795245193E+06
		1.77561728395E-03 \ 1.00553876720E+06
		1.91666666667E-03 \ 8.50353044339E+05
	}
	1.28E-03 \ 1.92E-03  	// Min \ Max equalizing flow
	8.5E+05 \ 1.44E+06		// Min \ Max Target pressure min \ max
	"T 19.2"				// Curve name
}

///////////////////////////////////////////
// From the Pneumatex equation, we transform to adapt to SI units.
// And in HySelect we use the curve with pman instead of p0.
// p0 =  -10.0*10^(-8.1)*qN^2.046+0.0004*qN+17.32-(qN/1000)^2/3.4^2									qN[l/h]  p0[bar]
// p0 = (-10.0*10^(-8.1)*(qN*3.6e6)^2.046+0.0004*qN*3.6e6+17.32-(qN*3600)^2/3.4^2)*100000			qN[m3/s] p0[Pa]
// pman = (-10.0*10^(-8.1)*(qN*3.6e6)^2.046+0.0004*qN*3.6e6+17.32-(qN*3600)^2/3.4^2+ 0.5)*100000	qN[m3/s] pman[Pa]
///////////////////////////////////////////

		1.54614197531E-03 \ 1.37070664728E+06   
		1.59907407407E-03 \ 1.33357365540E+06   
		1.65200617284E-03 \ 1.29489316068E+06   
		1.70493827160E-03 \ 1.25466378475E+06   
		1.75787037037E-03 \ 1.21288419078E+06   
		1.81080246914E-03 \ 1.16955308095E+06   
		1.91666666667E-03 \ 1.07823130428E+06   
	}

		#ePMFunc_Degasing | #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp							//Functions 			#ePMFunc_None/#ePMFunc_Degasing/#ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp/#ePMFunc_Compressor/#ePMFunc_Pump geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
		#ePMFunc_None														// FunctionsExclusion: #ePMFunc_None, #ePMFunc_Degasing, #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp, #ePMFunc_Compressor or #ePMFunc_Pump should be a geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
		#ePMVariant_EcoAuto | #ePMVariant_VacuumDegassing					//TecBox Variant		#ePMVariant_None/#ePMVariant_Cooling/#ePMVariant_EcoAuto/#ePMVariant_BreakTank/#ePMVariant_VacuumDegassing/#ePMVariant_ExternalAir/#ePMVariant_IntBufferVssl/#ePMVariant_HighFlowTemp
		30																	//TmaxWaterMakeUp		Max admissible temperature for WM (~30°C)
		NO_ID																//Identifier of the Pleno group that match the tecbox.
		NO_ID																//Identifier of the buffer vessel ID if fixed.
		NO_ID																//WaterTreatmentCombID	Identifier of the different combination of the water treatment.
		-1																	// MaxSecondaryVessels: Maximum allowed secondary vessel. If -1 we take the 'm_iMaxNumberOfVesselsInParallel' - 1 from the technical parameters.
	}
	200																		//SystemVolume		double (m3) for CPV,TV,..., vento
	1e5 \ 3e5																//WorkingPressRange	double Dpp for Vento
	5.5556e-5																//FlowWaterMakeUp		double (VNS in DE)
	-1.0																	//Kvs					double (Pleno P, Pi)
	#ePMPR_RefillNone														//Refillable			#ePMPR_RefillNone/#ePMPR_RefillOptional/#ePMPR_RefillMandatory	
	NO_ID																	//RefillGroupID
	0.0 \ -1.0 \ 0.08														// Identify what is the minimum vessel volume allowed with this Vento (See DataBObj.h for more details).
}

// DA 50

/////////////////
// *** 10-60 ****
/////////////////

new:CDB_DpController(DA50_32A\1) -> DPCONTR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0												// isDeleted
					1                                               // isAvailable
					0                                               // isHidden
					1                                               // isFix
					0                                               // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                               // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               								// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				1.6e+6 \ 2.5e+6                         		// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				PN_16-25                                        // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				150.0                                           // Tmax in °C
				-10.0                                           // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52780-132"                                 	// Reference to the TA Product
			"DA 50 DN32"                                    // Name of the product
			DPCTYPE_HIDP                                    // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_DA50                                        // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_STD                                        // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                               // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                              // Product comment
			"PX_DA50_32A"                                   // Product image ID
			ACCDPCGR_DA                                     // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                  // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID											// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                             // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       		// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID											// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_DUCTIRON                                    // Identifier of the body material
		DN_32                                           // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_FLANGE                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                                              // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                              // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		0                                               // CBI compatibility Index
		""                                              // CBI Version
		1.6e+6                                          // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone                                 // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone                                  // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_DA50_32A                                      // Identifier of the DpC characteristic
	#eDpCLoc_DownStream                             // DpC location: #DpCLoc_DownStream or #DpCLoc_UpStream
}

new:CDB_DpController(DA50_40A) -> DPCONTR_TAB
{ Inherited(DA50_32A)
	{
		CDB_Product::Reference	=	"52780-140"
		CDB_Product::Name			=	"DA 50 DN40"

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(MC15C-24) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{
    {
        {
            {
                {
                    0                                                   // isDeleted
                    1                                                   // isAvailable
                    0                                                   // isHidden
                    1                                                   // isFix
                    0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
                    0                                                   // Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
                    0                                                   // Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
                }
                0 \ DBL_MAX                                         // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
                NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID            Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
                DBL_MAX                                             // Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
                DBL_MIN                                             // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
            }
            "61015-011"                                         // Reference to the TA Product
            "TA-MC 15-C/24"                                     // Name of the product
            ACTTYP_ELEC                                         // Identifier of the actuator type
            ACTFAM_MC                                           // Identifier of the family of the product
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the actuator version
            7                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
            ""                                                  // Description of the product
            "NO_ID"                                             // Product image ID
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
            #ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
            NO_ID                                               // Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
            0.0                                                 // Price of the product
            #eProduct                                           // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
            0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth    
        }
        #eOPENTYPE_Linear                                   // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
        2.0e+2                                              // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
        -1.0                                                // Min. limited stroke of the actuator
        #eLimitedStrokeMode_No                              // Limited stroke mode of the actuator
        4.8e-3                                              // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
        NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the actuator adapter group
        0                                                   // Min temperature for operating environment in °C
        50                                                  // Max temperature for operating environment in °C
    }
    15000*                                              // List of actuating times separated by \ with default setting followed by * (in s/m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in s/90° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
    "40"                                                // Enclosure protection of the actuator in auto mode
    ""                                                  // Enclosure protection of the actuator when using manual override
    POW_24VAC \ POW_24VDC                               // List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
    FREQ_50-60                                          // Accepted frequency
    SIG_3POINT \ SIG_0-10V \ SIG_2-10V                  // List of accepted input control signals separated by \
    NO_ID                                               // List of accepted output control signals separated by \
	#eFailSafeNone								        // #eFailSafeNone, #eElectronicFailSafe, #eSpringReturn.
    1                                                   // 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
    RELAY_NO                                            // Type of relay.
    0                                                   // Number of binary input.
    #eDRP_None                                          // #eDRP_None, #eDRP_Extending, #eDRP_Retracting or #eDRP_Configurable.
}

// HYS-1997: IPI September 2022: Zeparo ZIMA - New EAN and Article No

new:CDB_Product(ACZIMA_50100) -> SEPACCESSOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			0										// isDeleted
			1                                       // isAvailable
			0                                       // isHidden
			1                                       // isFix
			0                                       // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                       // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               						// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                     	// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                                   // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		110.0                                   // Tmax in �C
		-10.0                                   // Tmin in �C
	}
	"788 0100"                              // Reference to the TA Product
	"ZIMA 50-100"                           // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_SEP                              // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_ZIZE                             // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID									// Identifier of the version of the product
	1										// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_ACZIMA_DESC"                       // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"									// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           		// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  		// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID									// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             		// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                             // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	0                                       // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID									// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
}

new:CDB_Product(ACZIMA_125200) -> SEPACCESSOR_TAB
{Inherited(ACZIMA_50100)
	{
		CDB_Product::Reference = "788 0200"
		CDB_Product::Name = "ZIMA 125-200"
	}
}

new:CDB_ValveCharacteristic(C_TPV-C15-3W\1) -> VALVE_CHAR_TAB
{
	{
		#eDISCRETE_False									// #eDISCRETE_True, #eDISCRETE_False or #eDISCRETE_Undefined
		#eTURN_Single                                       // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
		1.0													// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
	}
	1.0													// Min measurable setting (for TA-Scope)
	1.5                                                 // Min recommended setting (for selection)
	1                                                   // Number of curves: 0 = no curve; 1 = Kv catalogue only; 4 = Kv catalogue, Lambda, Re* and Kv from test.
	0.00 \ 0.00                                         // opening 1 \ Kv 1
	1.00 \ 0.05
	2.00 \ 0.15
	3.00 \ 0.25
	4.00 \ 0.56
	5.00 \ 0.70
	6.00 \ 1.10
}

		#eTURN_Single                                       // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
		1.0													// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
	}
	1.0													// Min measurable setting (for TA-Scope)
	1.5                                                 // Min recommended setting (for selection)

						0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
					}
					0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                     				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)

				}
				"52135-314"                             			// Reference to the TA Product

				#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
				NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
				0.0                                                 // Price of the product

			}
			BDY_GUNMETAL                                		// Identifier of the body material
			DN_15                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
			CONN_EUROCONE                                       // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
			NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
			NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID

			#eMeasDataNone                              		// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

		}

		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

			"EMO 1 0-10"                                 		// Name of the product

			ACTFAM_EMO                                  // Identifier of the family of the product
			NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the actuator version

			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.

			NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Linear                            // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
		1.8e+2                                       // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
		-1.0										 // Min stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_No						 // Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		4.5e-3                                       // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		NO_ID                                        // Identifier of the actuator adapter group
		DBL_MIN										 // Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		DBL_MAX										 // Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	25000*                                        // List of actuating times separated by \ with default setting followed by * (in s/m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in s/90° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
	"42"                                          // Enclosure protection of the actuator in auto mode
	""                                            // Enclosure protection of the actuator when using manual override
	POW_24VAC \ POW_24VDC                         // List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
	FREQ_50-60                                    // Accepted frequency
	SIG_0-10V                                     // List of accepted input control signals separated by \
	NO_ID                                         // List of accepted output control signals separated by \
	#eFailSafeNone								  // #eFailSafeNone, #eElectronicFailSafe, #eSpringReturn.
	0											  // 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
	RELAY_NO									  // Type of relay.
	0											  // Number of binary input.
	#eDRP_None									  // #eDRP_None, #eDRP_Extending, #eDRP_Retracting or #eDRP_Configurable.
}

			#ePartOfaSetNo                                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID													// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                     // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              					// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   				// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       				// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   				// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID													// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                      		// Identifier of the body material
		DN_40                                                   // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREADN                                            // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                                                      // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                      // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                      // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		0                                                       // CBI compatibility Index
		""                                                      // CBI Version
		0.0                                                     // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone                                         // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone                                          // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID													// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID													// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STS_40                                        		// Identifier of the valve characteristic
	NO_ID													// Identifier of the actuator group
}

			{
				{
					0														// isDeleted
					1                                                       // isAvailable
					0                                                       // isHidden
					1                                                       // isFix
					0                                                     	// Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                       // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               										// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				2.0e+6 \ 2.0e+6                         				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                   // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                   // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                   // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52149-550"                                           	// Reference to the TA Product
			"STS 2" NPT"                                          	// Name of the product
			SHUTTYPE_GLOBE                                      	// Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STS                                              	// Identifier of the family of the product

			#ePartOfaSetNo                                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID													// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                     // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              					// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both

			NO_ID													// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth

		BDY_AMETAL                                      		// Identifier of the body material
		DN_50                                                   // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREADN                                            // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID

				0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
			}
			1.0e+6 \ 1.0e+6								// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax  in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
			NO_ID										// Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
			70.0	        							// Tmax in °C
			5.0             							// Tmin in °C
		}
		"710 3012"									// Reference to the Product

				0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                         		// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                           // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				110.0                                           // Tmax in °C
				-10.0                                           // Tmin in °C
			}
			"789 1122"                                  	// Reference to the TA Product
			"ZUV 22"                                        // Name of the product
			SEPTYPE_MB                                      // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_ZUV                                         // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_STD                                        // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                               // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                              // Product comment
			"PX_ZUV_25"                                     // Product image ID
			ACCSEPGR_ZUV_2022                               // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                  // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID											// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                             // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       		// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID											// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_BRASS                                       // Identifier of the body material
		DN_20                                           // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_COMPRFIT                                   // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                                              // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                              // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		0                                               // CBI compatibility Index
		""                                              // CBI Version
		0.0                                             // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone                                 // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone                                  // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}

	0                                               // The number of magnet. 0 for separator without magnet.

		NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_ZIZE_200                                      // Identifier of the separator QDp characteristic
	0                                               // The number of magnet. 0 for separator without magnet.
}

//////////////////////////////////////////////
// Angle with PressFit Connection
//////////////////////////////////////////////

new:CDB_ThermostaticValve(HEIMSTD_15B) -> TRVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                 					// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                                               // Tmax in °C
						-10.0                                               // Tmin in °C
					}
					"2291-15.000"                       				// Reference to the TA Product
					"Standard 15(1/2")"                                 // Name of the product
					TRVTYPE_NOPRSET                                     // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_HEIMSTD                                         // Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_ANGLE                                          // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              				// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                   			// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                       			// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                   			// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID												// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
				}
				BDY_GUNMETALNIKPLT                      			// Identifier of the body material
				DN_15                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_RADUN_PFIT                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				""                                                  // CBI Version
				3.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                       		// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in ThermoCharID
		}
		2.00                                            	// Kvs of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_RVT                                              // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListNA                               	// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                            // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	C_HEIMSTD15                                         // Identifier of the thermostatic characteristic
	""                                                  // Description of the product
}

	PLENOGROUP_STATICO							// Identifier of the Pleno group that match the vessel.
	0.0											// PSch: not used in this case.
	0											// Accept Tecbox on top: 0/1.
}

new:CDB_ControlValve(316_15A) -> CTRLVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						0												// isDeleted
						1                                               // isAvailable
						0                                               // isHidden
						1                                               // isFix
						0                                               // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
						0                                               // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
						0               								// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
					}
					1.6e+6 \ 1.6e+6									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
					NO_ID                                           // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
					200.0                                           // Tmax in °C
					0.0                                             // Tmin in °C
				}
				"60336-815"										// Reference to the TA Product
				"CV 316 DN15"                                   // Name of the product
				CVTYPE_GLOBEIND                                 // Identifier of the valve type
				FAM_316                                         // Identifier of the family of the product
				VERS_STD                                        // Identifier of the version of the product
				1                                               // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
				""                                              // Product comment
				"TA_3WCV_M"                                     // Product image ID
				ACVGR_3XX15                                     // Identifier of the accessory group
				#ePartOfaSetNo                                  // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
				NO_ID											// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
				0.0                                             // Price of the product
				#eProduct                              			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
				NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
				0                                       		// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
				NO_ID                                   		// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
				NO_ID											// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
			}
			BDY_CASTIRON									// Identifier of the body material
			DN_15                                           // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
			CONN_FLANGE                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
			NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
			NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
			""                                              // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
			""                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
			""                                              // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
			0                                               // CBI compatibility Index
			""                                              // CBI Version
			0.0                                             // Maximum Dp of the valve
			#eMeasPointNone                                 // Measuring points
			#eMeasDataNone                                  // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
			NO_ID											// Identifier of the inlet size ID
			NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
		}
		NO_ID											// Identifier of the valve characteristic
	}
	2.5											    // Kvs of the CV
	2.0e-2                                          // Stroke of the CV
	50.0                                            // Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
	0.0001                                          // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
	COC_15D3                                        // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
	ACTGR_103-503                                   // Identifier of the actuator group
	NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the CV adapter group
	CP_3XX                                          // Identifier of the control properties
	#eCVAdapterListNA                               // Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                    // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
}

new:CDB_FlowLimitedControlValve(AEXACT_10A) -> FLCTRLVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                     				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						90.0                                                // Tmax in °C
						10.0                                                // Tmin in °C
					}
					"3911-01.000"                           			// Reference to the TA Product
					"A-exact 10(3/8")"                                  // Name of the product
					TRVTYPE_FLOWLIMITED                                 // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_AEXACT                                          // Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_ANGLE                                          // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              				// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                   			// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                       			// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                   			// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID												// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
				}
				BDY_GUNMETALNIKPLT                          		// Identifier of the body material
				DN_10                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_RADUN_THR                                      // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				""                                                  // CBI Version
				6.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                           	// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in FLCVCharID
		}
		0.0                                                 // Kvs of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_RVT                                              // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListNA                                   // Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                            // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	C_AEXACT                           					// Identifier of the flow limited control valve characteristic
	""													// Description of the product
}

new:CDB_FlowLimitedControlValve(AEXACT_15A) -> FLCTRLVALV_TAB

new:CDB_RegulatingValve(STAD-R15A_BV\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                                     		// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                       // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52273-215"                                             	// Reference to the TA Product
			"STAD-R 15"                                                 // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                                   // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STAD-R                                                  // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_DRAIN12                                                // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"PX_STAD25A_BV"                                             // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                                  // Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREAD                                                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STAD-R"                                                    // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"15"                                                        // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"1/2"                                                       // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		"5G"                                                        // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                        // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail		    // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD_R15													// Identifier of the valve characteristic
}
