{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                          	// isAvailable
					0                                                          	// isHidden
					1                                                          	// isFix
					1                                                          	// Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                          	// Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                                				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                      	// PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                      	// Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                      	// Tmin in °C
			}
			"52151-009"                                        			// Reference to the TA Product
			"STAD 10/09"                                               	// Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                                  	// Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STAD                                                   	// Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_NODRAIN                                               	// Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                          	// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                         	// Product comment
			"PX_STAD25A_BV"                                            	// Product image ID
			ACCREGVGR_STAD_NODRAIN                                     	// Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                             	// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                        	// Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                             		// Identifier of the body material
		DN_10                                                      	// Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREAD                                                	// Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                      	// Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                      	// Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STAD"                                                     	// Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"10/09"                                                    	// Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"3/8N"                                                     	// Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                          	// CBI compatibility Index
		"3A"                                                       	// CBI Version
		0.0                                                        	// Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                       	// Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail          	// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD010													// Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

// *** STADA ****

new:CDB_RegulatingValve(STADA10A_BV\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                     		// isAvailable
					0                                                     		// isHidden
					1                                                     		// isFix
					1                                                     		// Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                     		// Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                            					// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                  		// PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                  		// Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                  		// Tmin in °C
			}
			"52152-009"                                    				// Reference to the TA Product
			"STADA 10/09"                                          		// Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                              		// Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STADA                                              		// Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_NODRAIN                                           		// Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                      		// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                     		// Product comment
			"PX_STADA25A_BV"                                       		// Product image ID
			ACCREGVGR_STAD_NODRAIN                                 		// Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                         		// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                    		// Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                         			// Identifier of the body material
		DN_10                                                  		// Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREADM                                           		// Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                  		// Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                  		// Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STADA"                                                		// Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"10/09"                                                		// Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"3/8N"                                                 		// Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                      		// CBI compatibility Index
		"3A"                                                   		// CBI Version
		0.0                                                    		// Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                   		// Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail      		// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD010                                              		// Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

new:CDB_RegulatingValve(STADD1009A_BV\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                       	                // isAvailable
					0                                       	                // isHidden
					1                                       	                // isFix
					1                                       	                // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                       	                // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                             				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       	            // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                       	            // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                       	            // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52 552-209"                                     			// Reference to the TA Product
			"STAD-D 10/09"                                  	        // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                       	        // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STAD-D                                      	        // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_DOMWATER_DRAIN12                                    	// Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                               	        // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                              	        // Product comment
			"PX_STAD25B_BV"                                 	        // Product image ID
			ACCREGVGR_STAD_DRAIN                              	        // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                  	        // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                             	        // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETALTEAPLUS                                     		// Identifier of the body material
		DN_10                                               	    // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREAD                                         	    // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                               	    // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                               	    // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STAD-D"                                            	    // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"10/09"                                             	    // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"3/8N"                                              	    // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                   	    // CBI compatibility Index
		"3C"                                                	    // CBI Version
		0.0                                                 	    // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                	    // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail   	    // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD010                                               	// Identifier of the valve characteristic

	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                       // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52151-514"                                         		// Reference to the TA Product
			"STAD 1/2""                                                 // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                                   // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STAD                                                    // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_NODRAIN                                                // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"PX_STAD25A_BV"                                             // Product image ID
			ACCRVGR_STAD_NODRAIN_US                                     // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                              	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREADN                                                // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STAD"                                                      // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"15/14"                                                     // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"1/2N"                                                      // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		"3A"                                                        // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                        // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD015                                                   // Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

// *** STA with drain 1/2" (other versions are deleted) ****

new:CDB_RegulatingValve(STA15B_DRV) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					0                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0.6e+6 \ 2.0e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                       // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52150-214"                                         		// Reference to the TA Product
			"STA 15/14"                                                 // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_DRV                                                  // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STA                                                     // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_DRAIN12                                                // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"TA_DRV_L"                                                  // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID														// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                              	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREAD                                                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                                                          // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                          // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                          // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		0                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		""                                                          // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone                                             // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone                                              // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD015                                                   // Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

//************************************
// STS - With female thread and drain
//************************************

new:CDB_ShutoffValve(STS_15A\1) -> SHUTOFF_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0														// isDeleted
					1                                                       // isAvailable
					0                                                       // isHidden
					1                                                       // isFix
					0                                                     	// Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                       // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               										// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				2.0e+6 \ 2.0e+6                         				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                   // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120.0                                                   // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                   // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52149-615"                                           	// Reference to the TA Product
			"STS DN15"                                          	// Name of the product
			SHUTTYPE_GLOBE                                      	// Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STS                                              	// Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_DRAIN34                                            // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                       // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                      // Product comment
			"PX_STS"                                            	// Product image ID
			ACCGR_STS_1520_34                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID													// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                     // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              					// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   				// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       				// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   				// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID													// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_AMETAL                                      		// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                   // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_THREAD                                             // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                                                      // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                      // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                                                      // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		0                                                       // CBI compatibility Index
		""                                                      // CBI Version
		0.0                                                     // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone                                         // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone                                          // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID													// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID													// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STS_15                                        		// Identifier of the valve characteristic
	NO_ID													// Identifier of the actuator group
}

					}

			#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow 						// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.Avail

	{
		{
			#eDISCRETE_False									// #eDISCRETE_True, #eDISCRETE_False or #eDISCRETE_Undefined
			#eTURN_Multi                                        // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
			0.1													// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
		}
		1.0                                                 // Min measurable setting (for TA-Scope)
		7.5                                                 // Min recommended setting (for selection)
		1                                                   // Number of curves: 0 = no curve; 1 = Kv catalogue only; 4 = Kv catalogue, Lambda, Re* and Kv from test.
		0.00 \ 0.0                                          // opening 1 \ Kv 1
		1.00 \ 0.00
		2.00 \ 0.85
		3.00 \ 3.18
		4.00 \ 6.15
		5.00 \ 9.79
		6.00 \ 14.3
		7.00 \ 19.9
		8.00 \ 27.8
		9.00 \ 39.0
		10.0 \ 62.1
	}
	101.7												// Kvd = Kvs of the Dp controller
	2.5e+4                                              // Fc = Pressure drop in the throttle
	6.708333333e-3                                      // Max flow of the valve
	2                                                   // Number of curves: 0 = no curve; 1 = Qmax curve; 2 = Qmax and Dpmin curve
	0.0 \ 0.000000000e+0 \ 14900                        // Setting 1 \ qmax 1 \ Dpmin 1
	1.0 \ 0.000000000e+0 \ 15000
	2.0 \ 9.722222222e-5 \ 15200
	3.0 \ 3.638888889e-4 \ 15600
	4.0 \ 7.027777778e-4 \ 16000
	5.0 \ 1.105555556e-3 \ 16400
	6.0 \ 1.633333333e-3 \ 17000

				0 \ DBL_MAX								// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                   // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				100                                     // Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
				DBL_MIN                                 // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
			}
			"6740-00.500"                       	// Reference to the TA Product
			"IDS_VDX_HEAD"                          // Name of the product
			ACTTYP_THRMBUILTIN                      // Identifier of the actuator type
			ACTFAM_VDX_HEAD                         // Identifier of the family of the product
			ACTVER_STD                              // Identifier of the actuator version
			1										// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			"IDS_VDX_HEAD_A_DESC"                   // Description of the product
			"NO_ID"									// Product image ID
			NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID									// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                     // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                       // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID									// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Linear                       // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
		-1                                      // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
		-1                                      // Min. limited stroke of the actuator
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_No					// Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		-1                                      // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		NO_ID                                   // Identifier of the actuator adapter group
		DBL_MIN									// Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		50										// Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	6                                       // Min setting temperature (°C)
	28                                      // Max setting temperature (°C)
	-1                                      // Length of the capillary tube if exist
	-1                                      // Hysteresis in K
	6                                       // Frost protection temperature (°C)
}

		NO_ID                                                      	// Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID

		"3/4"                                                     	// Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II

				{
					0									// isDeleted

					0									// isHidden
					1									// isFix

					0									// Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               					// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				1e+6 \ 1e+6 						// in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID								// Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				65									// Tmax in �C
				0									// Tmin in �C
			}
			"813 1000"							// Reference to the Product
			"P"									// Name of the product
			TBXTYPE_PLENO						// Identifier of the product type
			TBXFAM_PLENO_P						// Identifier of the family of the product
			NO_ID								// Identifier of the version of the product
			1									// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""									// Product comment
			"NO_ID"	//TODO						// Product image ID
			NO_ID	//TODO						// Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo						// Boolean indicating if the valve is part of a ActSet
			NO_ID								// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.			
			0.0									// Price of the product
			#eProduct                       	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                           	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                               	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                           	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID								// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		"65"								// Enclosure protection
		POW_230VAC							// List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
		FREQ_50								// Accepted frequency
		20									// Power consumption
		0									// Sound pressure level only for compresso and vento
		0									// Nbre of compressors/pump 0/1/2 ( 0 for CX )
		NO_ID  								// PumpCompressCurveID
		-1.0								// Accuracy in Pascal
		#eWallHanged						// InstallationLayout: can be #eWallHanged, #eFloorStanding, #eFloorStandingNextTo, #eFloorStandingInFront, #eVesselTop or #eIntegrated
		0.2									// Height
		1.7									// Width
		0.125								// Depth
		3									// Weight double (kg)
		#ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp				// Functions: #ePMFunc_None, #ePMFunc_Degasing, #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp, #ePMFunc_Compressor or #ePMFunc_Pump geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
		#ePMFunc_None						// Functions exclusion: #ePMFunc_None, #ePMFunc_Degasing, #ePMFunc_WaterMakeUp, #ePMFunc_Compressor or #ePMFunc_Pump geometric progression 1,2,4,8,...
		#ePMVariant_None					// TecBox Variant: #ePMVariant_None/#ePMVariant_Cooling/#ePMVariant_EcoAuto/#ePMVariant_BreakTank/#ePMVariant_VacuumDegassing/#ePMVariant_ExternalAir/#ePMVariant_IntBufferVssl/#ePMVariant_HighFlowTemp/#ePMVariant_IntegratedPrimaryVessel
		65									// Max admissible temperature for WM (~30�C)
		NO_ID								// Identifier of the Pleno group that match the tecbox.
		NO_ID								// Identifier of the integrated vessel ID (type of integrated vessel is defined in the TecBox variant)
		NO_ID								// Identifier of the different combination of the water treatment.
		-1									// Maximum allowed secondary vessel. If -1 we take the 'm_iMaxNumberOfVesselsInParallel' - 1 from the technical parameters.
	}
	-1.0								// SystemVolume (m3) for CPV,TV,...
	-1.0 \ -1.0							// WorkingPressRangeMin \ WorkingPressRangeMax (Pa) for Pleno
	-1.0								// FlowWaterMakeUp (VNS in DE)
	0.5									// Kvs for Pleno P, Pi
	#ePMPR_RefillNone					// Refillable: #ePMPR_RefillNone/#ePMPR_RefillOptional/#ePMPR_RefillMandatory
	NO_ID								// Identifier of the Pleno Refill group that match the Pleno.
	-1.0 \ -1.0 \ -1.0					// Identify what is the minimum vessel volume allowed with this Vento (See DataBObj.h for more details).
}

// Remark for adapter for DN32 to DN50: As Gregor Bozic said in an email dated from 2016-05-24: "The spindle extension for DN32-50, is deliver with the valves
// and no adapter is needed for order. This code is for spare part in table. In the 65 to 150 you need to order 22413-001055.
// This is clear now, but you can't use the whole 22412-001055 adapter as the plate is screwed into valve. The new code is only spindle top.

				}
				0 \ DBL_MAX									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				100                                     	// Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C

			#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.

	-1                                      // Length of the capillary tube if exist
	0.3                                     // Hysteresis in K
	6                                       // Frost protection temperature (°C)

new:CDB_FlowLimitedControlValve(ECLIPSESD_10A) -> FLCTRLVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0 													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                     				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                                               // Tmax in °C
						-10.0                                               // Tmin in °C
					}
					"50 842-310"                           				// Reference to the TA Product
					"Eclipse S 10(3/8")"                                // Name of the product
					TRVTYPE_FLOWLIMITED                                 // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_ECLIPSE_SD                                      // Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_ANGLE                                          // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                       					// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                           					// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                               					// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                           					// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID												// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
				}
				BDY_BRASS                          					// Identifier of the body material
				DN_10                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_RADUN_THR                                      // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				""                                                  // CBI Version
				6.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                           	// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in FLCVCharID
		}
		0.0                                                 // Kvs of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_RVT                                              // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListNA                                   // Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
	                                                        // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	C_AEXACT                                            // Identifier of the flow limited control valve characteristic
	""		                                            // Description of the product
}

		NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth			
	}
	700.0e-3										// NominalVolume (m3)
	4.0e+5										// FactoryP0 (Pa)

	7.5e-1										// Diameter (m)
	290.0										// Weight (kg)
	#eFloorStanding								// FloorStanding: can be #eWallHanged, #eFloorStanding, #eFloorStandingNextTo, #eFloorStandingInFront, #eVesselTop or #eIntegrated

	NO_ID										// Identifier of the associated secondary vessel

new:CDB_ThermostaticValve(TRV2_10A_TRV\1) -> TRVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0													// isDeleted                                                                                             
							1                                                   // isAvailable                                                                                           
							0                                                   // isHidden                                                                                              
							1                                                   // isFix                                                                                                 
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6   									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used     
						120.0                                               // Tmax in °C                                                                                                                        
						-10.0                                               // Tmin in °C                                                                                                                        
					}
					"50861-110"  										// Reference to the TA Product                                                                                                                 
					"TRV-2 10"                                          // Name of the product                                                                                                                         
					TRVTYPE_PRESET                                      // Identifier of the valve type                                                                                                                
					FAM_TRV2                                            // Identifier of the family of the product                                                                                                     
					VERS_STRAIGHT                                       // Identifier of the version of the product                                                                                                    
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]                                                                                                      
					""                                                  // Product comment                                                                                                                             
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID                                                                                                                            
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group                                                                                                           
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              	            // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                      	        // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID										        // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
				}
				BDY_AMETAL 											// Identifier of the body material                                                                                                                                    
				DN_10                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size                                                                                                                              
				CONN_RADUN_THR                                      // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection                                                                                                                     
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID                                                                                                                   
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID                                                                                                        
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II                                                                                                                            
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II                                                                                                                            
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II                                                                                                                    
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index                                                                                                                                            
				""                                                  // CBI Version                                                                                                                                                        
				3.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve                                                                                                                                            
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.                                
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                    			// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in ThermoCharID
		}
		0.80												// Kvs of the CV                              
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV                           
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV                     
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic 
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group           
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group         
		CP_TRV                                              // Identifier of the control properties       
		#eCVAdapterListNA									// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                            // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).                                                                                        
	}
	C_TRV2												// Identifier of the thermostatic characteristic
	""					                                // Description of the product                   
}

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// HYS-1357 : IPI March 2020 (3): B&C: TA-Slider 160/500 BACnet/Modbus - With halogen free cables only 
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

//////////////////////////
// TA-Slider 160 Modbus CO
// Input signal: 0(2)-10 VDC
// With BUS communication (with binary input and relay change-over)
//////////////////////////


new:CDB_ElectroActuator(SLIDER160-MBCO1M) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			
			{
				{
					0											// isDeleted
					1                                           // isAvailable
					0                                           // isHidden
					1                                           // isFix
					0                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0 \ DBL_MAX									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120                                     	// Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
				DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
			}
			"322224-12511"								// Reference to the TA Product
			"TA-Slider 160 Modbus CO (1m)"              // Name of the product
			ACTTYP_ELEC                                 // Identifier of the actuator type
			ACTFAM_SLIDER                               // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_MODBUSCO                               // Identifier of the actuator version
			1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                          // Description of the product
			"NO_ID"										// Product image ID
			ACAGR_BACNET_MODBUS                         // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                       			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                               			// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Linear                           // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
		1.6e+2 \ 1.9e+2                             // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
		2.5e-4                                      // Min. limited stroke of the actuator
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_Electronic				// Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		6.5e-3                                      // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		NO_ID                               		// Identifier of the actuator adapter group
		0											// Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		50											// Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	10000*										// List of actuating times separated by \ with default setting followed by * (in s/m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
	"54"                                        // Enclosure protection of the actuator in auto mode
	""                                          // Enclosure protection of the actuator when using manual override
	POW_24VAC			                        // List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
	FREQ_50-60                                  // Accepted frequency
	SIG_MODBUS_RTU                       		// List of accepted input control signals separated by \
	NO_ID                       				// List of accepted output control signals separated by \
	#eFailSafeNone								// #eFailSafeNone, #eElectronicFailSafe, #eSpringReturn.
	0											// 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
	RELAY_CO									// Type of relay.
	1											// Number of binary input.
	#eDRP_None									// #eDRP_None, #eDRP_Extending, #eDRP_Retracting or #eDRP_Configurable.
}

	0.0 \ 0.000000000e+0 \ 20000                        // Setting 1 \ qmax 1 \ Dpmin 1

				CONN_FLANGE                                             // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                                   // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				"TA-FUSION-P"                                           // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				"100"                                                   // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				"4"                                                     // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				1                                                       // CBI compatibility Index
				"5G"                                                    // CBI Version
				8.0e+5                                                  // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                    // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail       // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID													// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID													// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID													// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in PICVCharID
		}
		144.7												// Kvs of the CV (Kvs is the Kv at full opening)
		2.0e-2				                                // Stroke of the CV
		">100"				                                // Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
		0.0					                                // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		COC_FUSION_P100		                                // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_FUSION_P32100                                 // Identifier of the actuator group
		ADPGR_FUSION_P65150	                                // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_FUSION_P65150	                                // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListSpecial								// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
		                                                    // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	CPICV_FUSION_P100                                   // Identifier of the PICV characteristic
}

	{
		CDB_HydroThing::Pmax 		=	2.5e+6 \ 2.5e+6
		CDB_Product::Reference	=	"22202-003100"
	}

// HYS-1475: IPI June 2012 - TC: F-Exakt production stop
new:CDB_ThermoCharacteristic(C_FEXAKT) -> VALVE_CHAR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			#eDISCRETE_True							// #eDISCRETE_True, #eDISCRETE_False or #eDISCRETE_Undefined
			#eTURN_Single                           // #eTURN_Single, #eTURN_Multi, #eTURN_Electronic or #eTURN_Undefined
			1.0										// Allows to know how to round the result of a computing setting.
		}
		0.0                                     // Min measurable setting (for TA-Scope)
		1.0                                     // Min recommended setting (for selection)
		1                                       // Number of curves
		0.00 \ 0.000                            // opening 1 \ Kv 1
		1.00 \ 0.017
		2.00 \ 0.041
		3.00 \ 0.063
		4.00 \ 0.114
		5.00 \ 0.187
		6.00 \ 0.350
	}
	0.00 \ 0.000 \ 0.000                    // Opening 1 \ Kv 1K \ Kv 2K \ ...
	1.00 \ 0.016 \ 0.017
	2.00 \ 0.038 \ 0.041
	3.00 \ 0.057 \ 0.063
	4.00 \ 0.095 \ 0.111
	5.00 \ 0.141 \ 0.177
	6.00 \ 0.215 \ 0.316
}

							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                 					// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)

					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.

				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

/////////////////////
// *** STAF-SGT **** (High temperature)
////////////////////
new:CDB_RegulatingValve(STAF-SGT020_BV\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				1.6e+6 \ 2.5e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				PN_16-25                                                    // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				150.0                                                       // Tmax in °C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52182-820"                                         		// Reference to the TA Product
			"STAF-SGT 20"                                               // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BV                                                   // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_STAF-SGT                                                // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_HIGHTEMP                                               // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"TA_BV"                                                     // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              	                	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                                       	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                      	            	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										            	// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_DUCTIRON                                            	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_20                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_FLANGE                                                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"STAF-SG"                                                   // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"20"                                                        // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"3/4"                                                       // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		"3A"                                                        // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                        // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_STAD020                                                   // Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

// HYS-1381
//////////////////
// *** DR16EVS ***
//////////////////

new:CDB_ControlValve(DR16EVS_25) -> CTRLVALV_TAB
{
    {
        {
            {
                {
                    {
                        0                                                // isDeleted
                        1                                               // isAvailable
                        0                                               // isHidden
                        1                                               // isFix
                        0                                                // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
                        0                                                // Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
                          0                                               // Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
                    }
                    d0.6e+6 \ 1.6e+6                                // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
                    NO_ID                                           // PNRangeID            Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
                    110.0                                           // Tmax in °C
                    -10.0                                           // Tmin in °C
                }
                "60431-025"                                        // Reference to the TA Product
                "DR 16 EVS DN25"                                // Name of the product
                CVTYPE_BUTFLY                                   // Identifier of the valve type
                FAM_DR16EVS                                     // Identifier of the family of the product
                VERS_STD                                        // Identifier of the version of the product
                1                                               // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
                "IDS_PN6_STATE_ORDERING"                        // Product comment
                "TA_2WCV_01"                                    // Product image ID
                ACVGR_DREVS25                                   // Identifier of the accessory group
                #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
                CVACTSET_TAB                                    // Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
                0.0                                             // Price of the product
                #eProduct                                       // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
                NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
                0                                               // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
                NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
                NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth    
            }
            BDY_CASTIRON                                    // Identifier of the body material
            DN_25                                           // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
            CONN_FLANGE                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
            NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
            NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
            ""                                              // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
            ""                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
            ""                                              // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
            0                                               // CBI compatibility Index
            ""                                              // CBI Version
            0.0                                             // Maximum Dp of the valve
            #eMeasPointNone                                 // Measuring points
            #eMeasDataNone                                  // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
            NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the inlet size ID
            NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the outlet size ID
        }
        NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the valve characteristic
    }
    36.0                                            // Kvs of the CV
    90.0                                            // Stroke of the CV
    25.0                                            // Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
    0.0                                             // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
    COC_DREVS25-40                                  // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
    ACTGR_M125-140                                  // Identifier of the actuator group
    NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the CV adapter group
    CP_DRX                                          // Identifier of the control properties
    #eCVAdapterListNA                               // Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                    // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
}

new:CDB_ControlValve(DR16EVS_32) -> CTRLVALV_TAB
{    Inherited(DR16EVS_25)
    {
        CDB_Product::Reference    =    "60431-032"
        CDB_Product::Name            =    "DR 16 EVS DN32"
        CDB_Product::AccessGroupID    =    ACVGR_DREVS32
        CDB_TAProduct::SizeID        =    DN_32
