new:CDB_ControlValve(DR16EVSAR_150) -> CTRLVALV_TAB
{
    {
        {
            {
                {
                    {
                        0                                                // isDeleted
                        1                                               // isAvailable
                        0                                               // isHidden
                        1                                               // isFix
                        0                                                // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
                        0                                                // Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
                          0                                               // Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
                    }
                    1.0e+6 \ 1.6e+6                                    // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
                    NO_ID                                           // PNRangeID            Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
                    110.0                                           // Tmax in °C
                    -10.0                                           // Tmin in °C
                }
                "60431-092"                                        // Reference to the TA Product
                "DR 16 EVSA/R DN150"                            // Name of the product
                CVTYPE_BUTFLY                                   // Identifier of the valve type
                FAM_DR16EVSAR                                   // Identifier of the family of the product
                VERS_STD                                        // Identifier of the version of the product
                1                                               // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
                ""                                              // Product comment
                "TA_2WCV_01"                                    // Product image ID
                ACVGR_DREVS150                                  // Identifier of the accessory group
                #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk                          // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
                CVACTSET_TAB                                    // Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
                0.0                                             // Price of the product
                #eProduct                                       // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
                NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
                0                                               // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
                NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
                NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth    
            }
            BDY_CASTIRON                                     // Identifier of the body material
            DN_150                                          // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
            CONN_FLANGE                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
            NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
            NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
            ""                                              // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
            ""                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
            ""                                              // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
            0                                               // CBI compatibility Index
            ""                                              // CBI Version
            0.0                                             // Maximum Dp of the valve
            #eMeasPointNone                                 // Measuring points
            #eMeasDataNone                                  // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
            NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the inlet size ID
            NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the outlet size ID
        }
        NO_ID                                            // Identifier of the valve characteristic
    }
    1945.0                                            // Kvs of the CV
    90.0                                            // Stroke of the CV
    25.0                                            // Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
    0.0                                             // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
    COC_DREVSAR150                                  // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
    ACTGR_OA8ASP25                                  // Identifier of the actuator group
    NO_ID                                           // Identifier of the CV adapter group
    CP_DRX                                          // Identifier of the control properties
    #eCVAdapterListNA                               // Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                    // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
}

new:CDB_Product(AT_DREVS_25A) -> ACTACCESSOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			0											// isDeleted
			1                                           // isAvailable
			0                                           // isHidden
			1                                           // isFix
			0                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX                             	// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C
		DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C
	}
	"68491-025"                                 // Reference to the TA Product
	"IDS_AT_CONS"                               // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_ACT                                  // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_MXXX                                 // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_DESC_AT_DREVS"                         // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  			// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             			// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	SER_ATCONS                                  // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	0                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                                      	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
}

			1                                           // isAvailable
			0                                           // isHidden
			1                                           // isFix
			0                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX                             	// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C
		DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C
	}
	"67007-002"                                 // Reference to the TA Product
	"IDS_AT_CONSCL"                             // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_ACT                                  // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_OAASXXX                              // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_DESC_AT_DREVSAR"                       // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  			// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             			// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	SER_ATCONSCL                                // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	0                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                                      	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
}

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Attachment groups for DR EVS/DR EVSA/DR EVSR valves
//
//        Rules:
//            ACXXXID \ &ACYYYID    // ACXXXID implies ACYYYID
//            ACXXXID \ !ACYYYID    // ACXXXID excludes ACYYYID
//            >ACXXXID              // ACXXXID is built-in
//            ^ACXXXID              // ACXXXID excludes all others
//		      *ACXXXID			    // ACXXXID two pieces should be included
//			  #ACXXXID			    // ACXXXID is distributed on each parent item (3 vessels (1 primary + 2 secondary) => 3 times the accessory).
//            +ACXXXID              // ACXXXID is an intersection between this group and an other. For this group accessory is NOT displayed
//            ++ACXXXID             // ACXXXID is an intersection between this group and an other. For this group accessory is displayed
//
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

new:CDB_RuledTable(ATGR_EVS_25) -> ACTACCGROUP_TAB
{
    {
        "AT DR 16 EVS DN25-40"
        0                        // 0/1: 1 if this table is the true parent of the IDs in it.
    }
    AT_DREVS_25A
    AT_DREVS_25B
    >AT_DREVS_25C
}

new:CDB_RuledTable(ATGR_EVS_50) -> ACTACCGROUP_TAB
{
    {
        "AT DR 16 EVS DN50-80"
        0                        // 0/1: 1 if this table is the true parent of the IDs in it.
    }
    AT_DREVS_50A
    AT_DREVS_50B
    >AT_DREVS_50C
}

//////////////
// M1XX series
// Electrical quater-tour actuator.
// Documentation can be found in the DR 16 EVS butterfly valve documentation (Dropbox (Hydronic College)\eR-D\Tech Docs\_Archives documentation\Control_valves\)
//////////////

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(M125) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{
    {
        {
            {
                {
                    0                                                   // isDeleted
                    1                                                   // isAvailable
                    0                                                   // isHidden
                    1                                                   // isFix
                    0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
                    0                                                   // Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
                    0                                                   // Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
                }
                0 \ DBL_MAX                                         // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
                NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID            Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
                DBL_MAX                                             // Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
                DBL_MIN                                             // Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
            }
            "65125-001"                                         // Reference to the TA Product
            "M125"                                              // Name of the product
            ACTTYP_ELEC                                         // Identifier of the actuator type
            ACTFAM_M                                            // Identifier of the family of the product
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the actuator version
            1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
            ""                                                  // Description of the product
            "NO_ID"                                             // Product image ID
            ACAGR_M125                                          // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
            #ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
            NO_ID                                               // Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
            0.0                                                 // Price of the product
            #eProduct                                           // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
            0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
            NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth    
        }
        #eOPENTYPE_Circular                                 // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
        2.5e+1                                              // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
        -1.0                                                // Min. limited stroke of the actuator
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_No                              // Limited stroke mode of the actuator
        90.0                                                // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
        NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the actuator adapter group
        0                                                   // Min temperature for operating environment in °C
        50                                                  // Max temperature for operating environment in °C
    }
    130*                                                // List of actuating times separated by \ with default setting followed by * (in s/m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in s/90° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
    "43"                                                // Enclosure protection of the actuator in auto mode
    ""                                                  // Enclosure protection of the actuator when using manual override
    POW_230VAC                                          // List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
    FREQ_50-60                                          // Accepted frequency
    SIG_3POINT                                          // List of accepted input control signals separated by \
    NO_ID                                               // List of accepted output control signals separated by \
	#eFailSafeNone								        // #eFailSafeNone, #eElectronicFailSafe, #eSpringReturn.
    1                                                   // 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
    RELAY_NO                                            // Type of relay.
    0                                                   // Number of binary input.
    #eDRP_None                                          // #eDRP_None, #eDRP_Extending, #eDRP_Retracting or #eDRP_Configurable.
}

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(M135I) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{ Inherited(M125)
    {
        CDB_Product::Reference    =                "65135-001"
        CDB_Product::Name        =                "M135 I"
        CDB_Actuator::MaxForceTorque=            3.5e+1
        CDB_Product::AccessGroupID=         ACAGR_M135
        CDB_ElectroActuator::ActuatingTimes=    130*
        CDB_ElectroActuator::IPxxAuto=            "54"
    }
}

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(M135II) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{ Inherited(M125)
    {
        CDB_Product::Reference    =                "65135-003"
        CDB_Product::Name        =                "M135 II"
        CDB_Actuator::MaxForceTorque=            1.5e+1
        CDB_Product::AccessGroupID=         ACAGR_M135
        CDB_ElectroActuator::ActuatingTimes=    70*
        CDB_ElectroActuator::IPxxAuto=            "54"
    }

// Product with modified ID
// Changed to ACA32_130 with a new article number 322042-10050
new:CDB_Product(ACA32_M125) -> ACTACCESSOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			0											// isDeleted
			1                                           // isAvailable
			0                                           // isHidden
			1                                           // isFix
			0                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX                             	// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C
		DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C
	}
	"67032-125"                                 // Reference to the TA Product
	"ACA32"                                     // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_ACT                                  // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_MXXX                                 // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_ACA32"                                 // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  			// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             			// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	SER_ACA32                                    // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	1                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                                      	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
}

		NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		DBL_MAX                                     // Tmax in °C
		DBL_MIN                                     // Tmin in °C
	}
	"67002-000"                                 // Reference to the TA Product
	"ACA2"                                      // Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_ACT                                  // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_OAASXXX                              // Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_ACA2"                                  // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  			// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             			// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	SER_ACA2                                    // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	1                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)

//****************************
// Copper NF A 49-145 tarif 1
//
// HYS-1621: It is in reality "Steel NF A 49-145 (T1)".
// Remark: the norm has been replaced by "EN 10255 (T1)". But we keep "NF A 49-145 (T1)" to not disturb french peoples.
// See in "Dropbox (eR-D)\eR-D\Tech Docs\Pipes\Series\" for more details.
//
// HYS-1621: It's not copper but well steel. But to not impact all old projects, we can't change the ID name.
// But we can put this series in the "tadb-deleted.txt" file. If user opens a file with this series, HySelect warns him that this
// project contains old pipe series. But user can continue and save his work with this series.
//

{
	"IDS_CU_NF_T1"

			{
				{
					{
						{
							0													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6                 					// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                                               // Tmax in °C
						2.0                                                 // Tmin in °C
					}
					"3441-01.000"                       				// Reference to the TA Product
					"Calypso 10(3/8")"                                  // Name of the product
					TRVTYPE_NOPRSET                                     // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_CALYPSO                                         // Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_ANGLE                                          // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              	            // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                      	        // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID										        // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
				}
				BDY_BRASSNIKPLT                         			// Identifier of the body material
				DN_10                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_RADUN_THR                                      // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				""                                                  // CBI Version
				2.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                       		// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in ThermoCharID
		}
		2.00                                            	// Kvs of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_RVT                                              // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListNA                               	// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                            // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	C_HEIMSTD10                                         // Identifier of the thermostatic characteristic
	""                                                  // Description of the product
}

			70.0	        							// Tmax in �C

					0                                                       // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               										// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				1.0e+6 \ 1.0e+6                         				// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                   // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used

			NO_ID													// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                     // Price of the product
			#eProduct                       						// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                           						// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)

			NO_ID                           						// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth

{

		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							0                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.0e+6   									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                                               // Tmax in �C
						-10.0                                               // Tmin in �C
					}
					"50 820-410"  										// Reference to the TA Product
					"Calypso ZERO 10"                                  	// Name of the product
					TRVTYPE_PRESET                                      // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_CALYPSOZ                                     	// Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_STRAIGHT                                       // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"TA_TRV"                                            // Product image ID
					ACCGR_RADCON_10                                     // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              	            // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                      	        // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID										        // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
				}
				BDY_BRASSLEADFREE									// Identifier of the body material
				DN_10                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_METRIC_THR                                     // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				""                                                  // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				""                                                  // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				0                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				""                                                  // CBI Version
				3.0e+4                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointNone                                     // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataNone                                      // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID											// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID											// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID                                    			// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in ThermoCharID
		}
		0.80												// Kvs of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Stroke of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Rangeability of the CV
		0.0                                                 // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_HEIM_TRV                                      // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_TRV                                              // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListNA									// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                                            // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	C_CALYPSOTRV3										// Identifier of the thermostatic characteristic
	""					                                // Description of the product
}

	}
	10000						// Minimum preset differential pressure.
	60000						// Maximum preset differential pressure.

new:CDB_DpReliefValve(DAB50PN10_1060_32A) -> DPCONTR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0							// isDeleted
					1                           // isAvailable
					0                           // isHidden
					1                           // isFix
					1                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					2                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               			// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				1.0e+6 \ 1.0e+6             // Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                    	// PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				150.0                       // Tmax in °C
				-10.0                       // Tmin in °C
			}
			"52 789-732"                // Reference to the TA Product
			"DAB 50 DN32"               // Name of the product
			DPCTYPE_DPRV                // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_DAB50         			// Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_STD               		// Identifier of the version of the product
			1                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                          // Product comment
			"NO_ID"                     // Product image ID
			NO_ID                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID						// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                   // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                       // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                       // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID						// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_DUCTIRON                // Identifier of the body material
		DN_32                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_ANSIFL                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                          // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                          // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                          // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                           // CBI compatibility Index
		""                          // CBI Version
		1.6e+6                      // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone				// Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone              // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID						// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID						// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	10000						// Minimum preset differential pressure.
	60000						// Maximum preset differential pressure.
}

		BDY_DUCTIRON                // Identifier of the body material
		DN_32                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_ANSIFL                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		""                          // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                          // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		""                          // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                           // CBI compatibility Index
		""                          // CBI Version
		1.6e+6                      // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointNone				// Measuring points
		#eMeasDataNone              // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID						// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID						// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	10000						// Minimum preset differential pressure.
	60000						// Maximum preset differential pressure.
}

// HYS-2041
//////////////////////////
// *** VEXVE TYPE 240 ****
//////////////////////////
// !!! VERS_FPM : FPM (Viton) o-rings

new:CDB_RegulatingValve(TA240-15A_BVS\1) -> REGVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				4.0e+6 \ 4.0e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				200.0                                                       // Tmax in �C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in �C
			}
			"6-52240-015"                                       		// Reference to the TA Product
			"TA-BVS 240 DN15"                                           // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BVSS                                                 // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_TA240                                                   // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_FPM                                                    // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"TA_BV"                                                     // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              	                	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                                       	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                      	            	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										            	// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_STSTEEL                                             	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_WELDING                                                // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"TA 240"                                                    // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"15"                                                        // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"1/2"                                                       // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		"3C"                                                        // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                        // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_TA240-1520                                                // Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

		{

					0															// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				4.0e+6 \ 4.0e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				200.0                                                       // Tmax in �C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in �C
			}
			"6-52140-015"                                       		// Reference to the TA Product
			"TA-BVS 140 DN15"                                           // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BVS                                                  // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_TA140                                                   // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_FPM                                                    // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"TA_BV"                                                     // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              	                	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                                       	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                      	            	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										            	// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_STEEL                                               	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_WELDING                                                // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"TA 140"                                                    // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"15"                                                        // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"1/2"                                                       // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
		1                                                           // CBI compatibility Index
		"3C"                                                        // CBI Version
		0.0                                                         // Maximum Dp of the valve
		#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                        // Measuring points
		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the inlet size ID
		NO_ID														// Identifier of the outlet size ID
	}
	C_TA240-1520                                                // Identifier of the valve characteristic
}

	{
		{
			{
				{
					0      														// isDeleted
					1                                                           // isAvailable
					0                                                           // isHidden
					1                                                           // isFix
					1                                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               											// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				4.0e+6 \ 4.0e+6                                 			// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				200.0                                                       // Tmax in �C
				-20.0                                                       // Tmin in �C
			}
			"6-52143-015"                                       		// Reference to the TA Product
			"TA-BVS 143 DN15"                                           // Name of the product
			RVTYPE_BVS                                                  // Identifier of the valve type
			FAM_TA143                                                   // Identifier of the family of the product
			VERS_FPM                                                    // Identifier of the version of the product
			1                                                           // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                                          // Product comment
			"TA_BV"                                                     // Product image ID
			NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID														// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                              	                	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                                                   	// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                                                       	// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                                      	            	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										            	// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
		}
		BDY_STEEL                                               	// Identifier of the body material
		DN_15                                                       // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
		CONN_FLANGE                                                 // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
		NO_ID                                                       // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
		"TA 143"                                                    // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"15"                                                        // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
		"1/2"                                                       // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II

		"3C"                                                        // CBI Version

		#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail           // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.

new:CDB_PIControlValve(FUSION_P32A\1) -> PICTRLVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						{
							0 													// isDeleted
							1                                                   // isAvailable
							0                                                   // isHidden
							1                                                   // isFix
							1                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
							0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
							0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
						}
						0.6e+6 \ 1.6e+6										// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
						NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
						120.0                                               // Tmax in °C
						-20.0                                               // Tmin in °C
					}
					"22202-001032" 										// Reference to the TA Product
					"TA-Fusion-P 32"                                    // Name of the product
					PICVTYPE_STD                                        // Identifier of the valve type
					FAM_FUSION_P                                        // Identifier of the family of the product
					VERS_STD                                            // Identifier of the version of the product
					1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
					""                                                  // Product comment
					"PX_FUSION_P50"                                     // Product image ID
					ACBCVGR_FUSION_P3250                                // Identifier of the accessory group
					#ePartOfaSetNo			                           	// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
					NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
					0.0                                                 // Price of the product
					#eProduct                              	            // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
					NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
					0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
					NO_ID                                      	        // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
					NO_ID										        // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
				}
				BDY_AMETAL											// Identifier of the body material
				DN_32                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
				CONN_THREAD                                         // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
				"TA-FUSION-P"                                       // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
				"32"                                                // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
				"1 1/4"                                             // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
				1                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
				"5G"                                                // CBI Version
				8.0e+5                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
				#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
				#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail	// Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
				NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
			}
			NO_ID												// MUST BE SET TO "NO_ID" -> valve characteristic is set now in PICVCharID
		}
		13.8												// Kvs of the CV (Kvs is the Kv at full opening)
		2.0e-2				                                // Stroke of the CV
		">100"				                                // Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
		0.0					                                // Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
		COC_FUSION_P3250	                                // Identifier of the close-off characteristic
		ACTGR_FUSION_P32100	                                // Identifier of the actuator group
		NO_ID			// See remark below					// Identifier of the CV adapter group
		CP_FUSION_P3250		                                // Identifier of the control properties
		#eCVAdapterListSpecial								// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
		                                                    // (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
	}
	CPICV_FUSION_P32									// Identifier of the PICV characteristic
}

// Remark for adapter for DN32 to DN50: As Gregor Bozic said in an email dated from 2016-05-24: "The spindle extension for DN32-50, is deliver with the valves
// and no adapter is needed for order. This code is for spare part in table. In the 65 to 150 you need to order 22413-001055.
// This is clear now, but you can’t use the whole 22412-001055 adapter as the plate is screwed into valve. The new code is only spindle top.

new:CDB_Product(ACSTEMHEATER_40_50) -> VALVEACCESSOR_TAB
{
	{
		{
			0											// isDeleted
			1                                           // isAvailable
			0                                           // isHidden
			1                                           // isFix
			0                                           // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
			0                                           // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
			0               							// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
		}
		0 \ DBL_MAX                             	// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
		NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
		50                                     		// Tmax in �C
		-10                                     	// Tmin in �C
	}
	"322042-80011"                             	// Reference to the TA Product
	"IDS_ACSTEMHEATER_TAMOD4050_DESC"			// Name of the product (can be an IDS)
	ACCTYP_VALVE                                // Identifier of the type of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	ACCFAM_STEMH								// Identifier of the family of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the version of the product
	1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
	"IDS_ACSTEMHEATER_DESC"                     // IDS of a more verbose description of the accessory
	"NO_ID"										// Product image ID		
	NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory group
	#ePartOfaSetNo                  			// Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
	NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
	0.0                             			// Price of the product
	#eAccessory                              	// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
	NO_ID                                  		// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
	0                                           // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
	NO_ID                                      	// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
	NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
}

// HYS-2077: Delete TBV-C/CM Kits.
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
//		Table BCVACTSET_TAB : Control valve/Actuator sets
// When reading CDB_Set object (txt file) TAS4 will update
// First and Second ID, TA_Product::PartOfASet member variable
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
//	new:CDB_Set(ID)->BCVACTSET_TAB
//	{
//		{
//			0				isDeleted
//			1				isAvailable
//			0				isHidden
//			1				isFix
//			0				Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation )
//			0				Free integer (bit 0: NotForIndSel, bit 1: NotForDirSel, bit 2: NotForHMCalc)
//      	0               Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
//		}
//		"Reference"			Reference to the TA Product
//		"Name"				Name of the product
//		FirstID				Identifier of the control valve
//		SecondID			Identifier of the actuator
//		AccessGroupID		Identifier of the accessory group
//		"Parameter"			String to allow to apply some filter.
//		"NextID"			Identifier of the next ID to consider can be Set ID, Group ID, Product ID etc...
//	}
// Inherited Fields
//	CDB_Thing::Deleted
//	CDB_Thing::Available
//	CDB_Thing::Hidden
//	CDB_Thing::Fixed
//	CDB_Thing::FreeInt1
//	CDB_Thing::FreeInt2
//	CDB_Thing::SorTInt
//	CDB_Set::Reference
//	CDB_Set::Name
//	CDB_Set::FirstID
//	CDB_Set::SecondID
//	CDB_Set::AccGroupID
//	CDB_Set::Parameter
//	CDB_Set::NextID
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

///////////////////////////
// *** TBV-C sets ***

new:CDB_ControlValve(TBV-C15LFF_TV\1) -> BALCTRLVALV_TAB
{
	{
		{
			{
				{
					{
						0													// isDeleted
						1                                                   // isAvailable
						0                                                   // isHidden
						1                                                   // isFix
						1                                                   // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
						0                                                   // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
						0               									// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
					}
					0.6e+6 \ 1.6e+6										// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
					NO_ID                                               // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
					120.0                                               // Tmax in °C
					-20.0                                               // Tmin in °C
				}
				"52433-115"											// Reference to the TA Product
				"TBV-C 15LF"                                        // Name of the product
				RVTYPE_BVC                                          // Identifier of the valve type
				FAM_TBV-C                                           // Identifier of the family of the product
				VERS_STD                                            // Identifier of the version of the product
				1                                                   // Level of priority for selection [1,10]
				""                                                  // Product comment
				"PX_TBV-C20"                                        // Product image ID
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the accessory group
				#ePartOfaSetNo                                      // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
				NO_ID												// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
				0.0                                                 // Price of the product
				#eProduct                              	            // #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
				NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
				0                                                   // 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
				NO_ID                                      	        // Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
				NO_ID										        // Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth	
			}
			BDY_AMETAL											// Identifier of the body material
			DN_15                                               // Identifier of the corresp. valve size
			CONN_SMTHEND                                        // Identifier of the (inlet/pipe side) connection
			NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the connection table, can be NO_ID
			NO_ID                                               // Identifier of the outlet/body side connection, can be NO_ID
			"TBV-C"                                             // Type of the valve as used in the CBI II
			"15LF"                                              // Size of the valve as used in the CBI II
			"1/2LF"                                             // Size of the valve in inch as used in the CBI II
			1                                                   // CBI compatibility Index
			"4A"                                                // CBI Version
			1.0e+5                                              // Maximum Dp of the valve
			#eMeasPointInlet | #eMeasPointOutlet                // Measuring points. #eMeasPointNone or a combination of #eMeasPointInlet, #eMeasPointOutlet, #eMeasPointMeasStatOut or #eMeasPointP+.
			#eMeasDataDp | #eMeasDataFlow | #eMeasDataDpAvail   // Measurable data. #eMeasDataNone or a combination of #eMeasDataDp, #eMeasDataFlow, #eMeasDataDpSignal, #eMeasDataDpAvail, #eMeasDataDpStab or #eMeasDataDpCAlwaysOn.
			NO_ID												// Identifier of the inlet size ID
			NO_ID												// Identifier of the outlet size ID
		}
		C_TBV-C15LF											// Identifier of the valve characteristic
	}
	0.90												// Kvs of the CV
	4.0e-3		                						// Stroke of the CV
	0.0			                						// Rangeability of the CV, introduce as a double or as a string ">100" only '>' is supported
	0.0			                						// Leakage rate of the CV as a fraction of Kvs
	COC_TBV-C15	                						// Identifier of the close-off characteristic
	ACTGR_TBV_C	                						// Identifier of the actuator group
	NO_ID		                						// Identifier of the CV adapter group
	CP_TBV-C	                						// Identifier of the control properties
	#eCVAdapterListNA           						// Set what is the method to use to retrieve adapter list linked to this control valve (#eCVAdapterListNormal or #eCVAdapterListSpecial).
                                						// (see enum in 'tadb.txt' for more description).
}

// HYS-2087: phase-out of Slider 1250

//////////////////////////
// TA-Slider 1250 standard
// Input signal: 0(2)-10 VDC, 0(4)-20 mA, 3-point, on-off
//////////////////////////

new:CDB_ElectroActuator(SLIDER1250-STD-24) -> ACTUATOR_TAB
{
	{
			
		{
			{
				{
					0																				// isDeleted
					1                                                                               // isAvailable
					0                                                                               // isHidden
					1                                                                               // isFix
					0                                                                               // Integer for flagging b31...b0 (bit 0: InCbi, bit1: available for Hub, bit2: available for HubStation)
					0                                                                               // Integer to exclude product for selection: 1 (Individual/Batch), 2 (Direct) or 4 (HMCalc).
					0               																// Sort integer (Allow to show a group of articles in the order defined with this variable).
				}
				0 \ DBL_MAX									// Pmaxmin and Pmaxmax in Pa (if Pmaxmin = PN6, Pmaxmin is not used in PN string; a 'd' in front of Pmaxmin enforces it in PN string)
				NO_ID                                       // PNRangeID			Identifier of CDB_RuledTable that contains available PN, could be NO_ID in this case Pmaxmin/max are used
				120                                     	// Tmax in °C: Max media temperature in °C
				0                                     		// Tmin in °C: Min media temperature in °C
			}
			"322227-10110"                              // Reference to the TA Product
			"TA-Slider 1250 (24V)"                      // Name of the product
			ACTTYP_ELEC                                 // Identifier of the actuator type
			ACTFAM_SLIDER                               // Identifier of the family of the product
			NO_ID                                       // Identifier of the actuator version
			1											// Level of priority for selection [1,10]
			""                                          // Description of the product
			"NO_ID"										// Product image ID
			ACAGR_SLIDER1250                            // Identifier of the actuator accessory group
			#ePartOfaSetNo                              // Boolean indicating if product is part of a set. Can be #ePartOfaSetNo, #ePartOfaSetYes, #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOk or #ePartOfaSetYesBreakOnMsg.
			NO_ID										// Table ID where are sets if exist for the current product.
			0.0                                         // Price of the product
			#eProduct                       			// #eProduct, #eAccessory, #eBoth Integer to indicate if the Product is only Product, only Accessory or both
			NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the series of the accessory (mainly used in DlgDirSel)
			0                               			// 0/1: 1 if accessory cannot be ordered separately (for DlgDirSel)
			NO_ID                           			// Identifier of the accessory type if #eBoth 
			NO_ID										// Identifier of the accessory family if #eBoth
		}
		#eOPENTYPE_Linear                           // Opening type (Linear or Circular)
		12.5e+2                                     // Max force or torque developped by the actuator
		1.0e-3                                   	// Min. limited stroke of the actuator
		#eLimitedStrokeMode_Electronic				// Limited stroke mode of the actuator
		2.0e-2                                      // Max stroke of the actuator (in m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
		ADPGR_SLD_1250								// Identifier of the actuator adapter group
		0											// Min temperature for operating environment in °C
		50											// Max temperature for operating environment in °C
	}
	3000 \ 4000 \ 6000 \ 8000 \ 12000 \ 16000*                                      // List of actuating times separated by \ with default setting followed by * (in s/m for #eOPENTYPE_Linear; in ° for #eOPENTYPE_Circ)
	"54"                                                                            // Enclosure protection of the actuator in auto mode
	""                                                                              // Enclosure protection of the actuator when using manual override
	POW_24VAC \ POW_24VDC                                                           // List of accepted Power supplies separated by \
	FREQ_50-60                                                                      // Accepted frequency
	SIG_ON-OFF \ SIG_3POINT \ SIG_0-10V \ SIG_2-10V \ SIG_0-20mA \ SIG_4-20mA       // List of accepted input control signals separated by \
	SIG_0-10V \ SIG_2-10V                                                           // List of accepted output control signals separated by \
	#eFailSafeNone																	// #eFailSafeNone, #eElectronicFailSafe, #eSpringReturn.
	1																				// 1 if a 3 points or proportional actuator can work in On/Off mode otherwise 0.
	RELAY_NO																		// Type of relay.
	0																				// Number of binary input.
	#eDRP_None																		// #eDRP_None, #eDRP_Extending, #eDRP_Retracting or #eDRP_Configurable.
}

	{
